# Line-ending policy. This repo is developed on Windows and built/tested on Linux,
# so line endings are not cosmetic here.
#
# Without this file, a clone with core.autocrlf=true (the Windows default) rewrites
# checked-out files to CRLF. A shell script with CRLF fails in Linux with a
# baffling error -- the shebang becomes "#!/usr/bin/env bash\r", so the kernel
# looks for an interpreter literally named "bash\r" and reports
# "bad interpreter: No such file or directory", or lines fail with "$'\r': command
# not found". Pinning eol per type makes the working tree correct on both.

# Default: let Git normalise text in the repository, and decide eol per type below.
* text=auto

# Must be LF -- these run inside Linux containers / CI.
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf

# Must be CRLF -- cmd.exe is the only consumer and it is happiest with CRLF.
*.cmd       text eol=crlf
*.bat       text eol=crlf

# Binary: never touch.
*.pem       -text
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.tif       binary
